    <title class="- topic/title ">Step 6: Verify the Image</title>
    <body>
        <div id="tcc-vtune-verify-image"/>
        <div id="step-6-verify-the-image">
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>After the system reboots, open a terminal window and run the
                    following commands to verify that the directory
                    <codeph>/opt/intel/vtune_profiler_drivers/</codeph> exists and contains the
                    <codeph>insmod-sep</codeph> file. (If not, the image was built incorrectly.)</p>
                    <codeblock>cd /opt/intel/vtune_profiler_drivers/
                        ls -la</codeblock>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Enable the system to automatically load the Intel® VTune™ Profiler
                    drivers at boot time:</p>
                    <codeblock>cd /opt/intel/vtune_profiler_drivers/
                        ./boot-script --install</codeblock>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Reboot the system.</p>
                    <codeblock>reboot</codeblock>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>After the system reboots, open a terminal window and run the
                    following command to verify that the Intel® VTune™ Profiler drivers
                    loaded:</p>
                    <codeblock>lsmod | grep -E 'socwatch|vtsspp|sep|socperf|pax'</codeblock>
                    <p>Your output should look something like this:</p>
                    <codeblock>socwatch2_11           69632  0
                        vtsspp                344064  0
                        sep5                  897024  0
                        socperf3              589824  2 sep5,socwatch2_11
                        pax                    16384  0
                        ...</codeblock>
                </li>
            </ol>
            <note>
                <p>To disable automatic driver loading, use the <codeph>--uninstall</codeph> option: <codeph>./boot-script --uninstall</codeph></p>
            </note>
        </div>
    </body>
